cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL

The paper proposes a novel approach for unsupervised feature selection in high-dimensional data, which is a common problem in many areas such as computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed method also involves autoencoder regression, which is a popular technique in neural networks, suggesting cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper presents experimental results on benchmark datasets, indicating that it involves empirical evaluation, which is common in natural language processing, leading to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as a possible sub-category.
